						<p>The record is damaged and dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 918, Durmukhi, Śrāvaṇa, śu. 5 • • • spativāra</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 996, July 23 Thursday</hi> and refers itself to the reign of the Chālukya king <hi rend="bold">Āhavamalladēva</hi> (Taila II). It records the grant of a garden in the presence of the chief of the <hi rend="bold">[Kārttikēya]-tapōvana</hi> and the five <hi rend="italic">Vargas</hi> of the village <hi rend="bold">Koṭṭi[toṇe].</hi></p>						

